<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showMessage?topicID=585.topic">pub94.ezboard.com/ffirion...=585.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p><b>Pixxii <br>Pixxii's me name. Mischief's me game.<br>
Putting Nillipus out of work for 40+ seasons so far.<br>
<i>Pixxii tosses some pixie dust your way---oops, that's sugar! <br>You have been pixxiied!<b></i></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sillypixxii>Silly Pixxii</A> at: 12/3/02 2:40:53 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=isharramoonsong>Isharra Moonsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 611<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/3/02 2:39:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=326.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~brennec/_uimages/Isharra.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Dreamwalker</span><hr size=1> Lord Thule had asked me where I wished to re-enter the world, and in an instant I chose Felwithe. It had been too long since I had seen my father, and for all I knew, he believed me dead. So, the Lord of Dreams used his powers to restore me to the flesh with one final warning that he knew not what sort of side effects could result from being restored to life from the world of Dreams.<br>
<br>
So, my eyes flutter open to see a room, apparently in an inn, and hopefully an inn in Felwithe. I rise, unsure of how I will appear in physical form, since in Lord Thule's realm I could wear whatever I conjured in my mind. I look down at myself and chuckle, shaking my head and rolling my eyes. &quot;Very funny, my lord,&quot; I grumble, patting down the multi-colored fabric of my new jester's tunic.<br>
<br>
Looking around the room, I find a small pack of essentials: food and drink and, har dee har har, a jester's cap. A groan escapes my lips, but I can't help but smile. <br>
<br>
A short walk to the bank and back to the inn and I'm clothed more appropriately for a day in court, dressed in dark green silk with a dropped waist and a belt of pearls. I dress before the mirror, thinking I don't look so bad for a dead woman,  when my eyes slip down to the black stain on my neck--the brand of the Iksar Empire. A chill flowing through me, I lift my hand and knock twice on the wooden washstand. <br>
<br>
Presently, out of the corner of my eye I glimpse something moving in the mirror. Startled, I swing about, but nothing seems to be there. My imagination, of course, or at least that's what I tell myself. <br>
<br>
Strapping a dainty purse to my belt and draping my shoulders in a burgundy shawl, I realize how late it is getting. Nightfall will soon arrive, and I haven't even begun the walk for my father's manse. It will be a late night, I realize, but after dreaming for such a long time, it will be nice to be awake and gaze upon the real stars once more.<br>
<br>
I pay the innkeep on my way out, and he greets me with surprise. He had not known I was staying at the inn, and the room I claim to have rented had been out of order for quite a while. But he'll take my coin anyway, if I insist, and he thanks his Lady with great humility, and I leave, uncomfortable with his bowing and scraping.  I'd forgotten what it was like to be treated like a Lady of the court.<br>
<br>
My steps carry me down the lane and toward the grander estates of Felwithe. I am about to turn up the cobbled roadway that leads to my father's estate when I spy a nude elf, walking along with some scrolls under his arm, as if nothing were extraordinary about his garb---or lack thereof. I feel my cheeks pinken and I try not to stare, but he catches my eye and nods to me cheerfully, then continues on his way. This is when I notice that there are others walking past him, not even glancing his way. I pause in my journey and stare in earnest now, for some sign that someone else finds a nude elf walking down the center of the street a bit odd. But no one else seems to notice.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>What has happened to my fair city?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I wonder, stunned, as I tear my eyes from the elf. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> I've been away much too long, </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> I muse as I hurry up to the doorway of my father's----and my---home.<br>
<br>
